biography.text: Common is an artist, actor, and activist. Most recently, Common is making his broadway debut in Between Riverside and Crazy. With a storied career spanning three decades, his work has been recognized with numerous GRAMMY® Awards, as well as an Emmy® and an Academy® Award for the song "Glory (From the Motion Picture Selma)," which he co-wrote and performed with John Legend. In the fall of 2020 and 2021, he released his 2-part album: A Beautiful Revolution Pt. 1 & 2.
